## 7) Appendix — key code & sample responses ### Example: `POST /api/amenities-report/` request (JSON) { "lat": 27.67833, "lng": 85.312612, "radius": 1000 }
### Example: `GET /api/area-population/?lat=...&lng=...&radius=4000` response (excerpt) { "location": { "lat": 27.67833, "lng": 85.312612 }, "radius": 4000.0, "total_population": 570889, "affected_wards": [ {"ward_number": 1, "population": 21145, "population_density": 12152.0, "area_sqkm": 1.74}, ... ] }
### Note on accuracy Current population estimate is conservative (sums full ward populations when a ward intersects the buffer). To report more precise localized population, compute intersection area fractions after reprojecting geometries to a metric CRS.
